    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 10</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut010-P297v-L15_trl" n="15"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.009.trl.xml#Deut009-P297v-L15_trl" />
                        <l n="1">At that time
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the Lord said to me, ‘Cut yourself two tablets of stone
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             like the first ones, and come up to me at the mountain, and make
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             a chest of wood.</l>
                        <l n="2">And I will write on the tablets
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             the words that were on the first
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             tablets which you broke, and you shall put them in the chest.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="3">And I made an ark of acacia wood,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="298r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and I cut two tablets of stone like the first ones, and I went up
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             the mountain, and the two tablets were in my hand.</l>
                        <l n="4">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             And he wrote on the tablets like the first writing:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             the ten commandments, which the Lord spoke to you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             on the mountain from the midst of the fire in the day of the assembly.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             And the Lord gave them to me.</l>
                        <l n="5">And I turned
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             myself and came down from the mountain and put the tablets
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             in the ark that I had made. And they have been there, as the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             commanded me.</l>
                        <l n="6">And the children of Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             set out from Beeroth-Bene-Jaakan to Moserah. There
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             Aaron died and there he was buried. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             Eleazar, his son, served as priest in his place.</l>
                        <l n="7">From there
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             they set out to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             a land of rivers of waters.</l>
                        <l n="8">When I asked for atonement
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             because of the sin of the calf, at that time
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the Lord set apart the tribe of Levi, to carry the ark
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             of the covenant of the Lord, to stand before the Lord to serve
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             him and to bless Israel in his name, to this
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             day.</l>
                        <l n="9">Therefore Levi has no portion or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             share with his brothers. The Lord: he is his portion, as
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             the Lord your God spoke to him.</l>
                        <l n="10">And I stood
                            <milestone unit="page" n="298v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             in the mountain as in the first days: forty days and forty nights.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And the Lord listened to me at that time as well. The Lord did not want
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             to crush you.</l>
                        <l n="11">And the Lord said to me, “Rise,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             set out on the journey before the people, that they may come and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             inherit the land which I swore to their fathers to give
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             to them.”</l>
                        <l n="12">And now, oh Israel, what the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             your God wants from you is but to fear the Lord your God,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             to walk in all his ways and to love him and to serve
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul,</l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             To keep the commandments of the Lord and his statutes which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             I command you today to be good for you.</l>
                        <l n="14">Lo,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             the skies — and the rows of skies — are under the Lord your God’s rule,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             and the earth and everything that is in it.</l>
                        <l n="15">Only, the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Lord had a delight in your fathers, to love them, and he chose their
                            offspring
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             after them: you, better than all the peoples, as it is this day.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="16">And you shall circumcise the foreskin of your heart
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and you shall not harden your neck anymore.</l>
                        <l n="17">Because the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             your God: he is the God of angels and the Lord of globes,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             a great God, mighty and awesome, who does not favour
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and takes no bribe.</l>
                        <l n="18">He
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             is doing judgement for the orphan and the widow and loves the stranger,
                            to give
                            <milestone unit="page" n="299r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             him food and clothing.</l>
                        <l n="19">So you shall love the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             stranger, because you were strangers in the land of Egypt.</l>
                        <l n="20">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             You shall fear the Lord your God, you shall serve him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             and you shall cling to his Law, and you shall swear to the truth by his
                            name.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="21">He is your praise and he is your God, who has done
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             these great and awesome things with you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             which your eyes have seen.</l>
                        <l n="22">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             Your fathers went down to Egypt with seventy souls, and now the Lord
                            your God has made you
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut010-P299r-L9_trl" n="9"
                                next="ADub.III.73.005.011.trl.xml#Deut011-P299r-L9_trl" />
                             like the stars of the skies for multitude. </l>
                    </ab>
